Only some 15 facts about Gujarat which no media house told you ever 
------------------------------------------------------ 1. The only state in 
India which has the infrastructure to provide E-services through IT to 
13685 Gram Panchayats which are connected through Gujarat State Wide Area 
Network (GSWAN). 2. India’s first 1 MW Canal-top Solar Power Project on the 
Canal of the Sardar Sarovar Project ( eliminating the need for separate 
land for solar plants ) 3. Gujarat accounts for 15.14% (USD 114.52 bn) of 
the total investments in India; Highest amongst all States in India. 4. 
Gujarat is set to become the first state in the country to have a complete 
integrated police ERP (enterprise resource planning, a software integrating 
all aspects of an operation). 5. Nearly 100% of Gujarat’s 18,000 villages 
have electricity connection for 24hr power through the Jyotigram Yojana. 6. 
Gujarat tourism, attracting 1.65 crore visitors annually had numbers 
ranging to 20 lakh during years 2001-02, 25 million tourists visited Gujrat 
in the FY 2012-13. 7. Gujarat has one of the best rural road networks in 
India, and 98.7% of villages are connected by pukka roads. 8. Under scheme 
called "Green Kisan Credit Card", govt convinced banks to consider the 
monetized value of teak trees owned by the tribal farmers and give them 
loans against the mortgage of these trees. ( first ever in world to have 
tree as a guarantee ) 9. In 2007, the number for malnourished children in 
gujarat was 70.69 % (highest in country) , but by 2011, the number came 
down to 38.77 % ( most improved state in country ) 10. Before Narendra Modi 
became CM, the state’s average growth in GDP was 2.8%. Under him, between 
2002-03 and 2011-12, it turned out to be 10.3%. 11. In 2004-05, 33% of 
Gujarat's population were under below poverty line , in 2011-12 it dropped 
to 15% ( sharpest improvement in country ) 12. Gujarat was awarded the 
prestigious 'UN Sasakawa' award for outstanding work in the field of 
disaster management and risk reduction (no other Indian state got it ever ) 
13. Gujarat has largest OFC (optical fiber connection) network of more than 
50,000 km. There are more than 900,000 internet users and all villages are 
connected with broadband internet. 14. The state registered 12.8% 
agriculture growth in the last five years against the national average of 
2%. (consistent average of above 10% over a decade) 15. The region of kutch 
in Gujarat was synonym to "drought" , this region now boasts 32% annual 
growth , second to Surat, the richest city there. Not to mention the 
exemplary industrial growth, 24x7 power supply , safe and riot free 
environment !! Let the "Kejriwaal bluff-masters" first prove themselves and 
then raise fingers at others﻿

Water subsidy
----------------
The subsidy is fiscally unwise, short-termist, and ignores the poor who 
lack access to piped water

It lavishes free water upon those who can afford to pay, and should pay. 
The poorest of the Delhi have been kept out of the water subsidy scheme.

Approximately 52 per cent of water is lost because of the Delhi Jal Board's 
(DJB's) leaky distributional pipeline. Money should have been spent wisely 
in improving the infrastructure.

Delhi has about 18 lakh water connections. Of these 8.5 lakh have 
functional meters. About 5 lakh meters are non-functional or defective. The 
rest are un-metered. A very large number of jhuggis in Delhi have no water 
connection and are not covered by the free water scheme.


Electricity subsidy & audit of discoms
------------------------------------------
Discoms are already sitting on losses worth Rs 11,000 crore. Bringing down 
revenue will result in further power outages.

The government cannot interfere in tariff fixation. It is a regulatory 
issue.

The tariff is fixed after due diligence and it is difficult to reduce 
tariff beyond a point as 70% of Delhi’s power comes from outside and the 
board has no control over the cost of power- This is as per state power 
watchdog.

There is no way a political party can interfere with the tariff fixed by 
DERC. The rate fixed by them can either be rejected or accepted by the 
government of the state. In case if it rejects the rate, government will 
have to compensate the companies selling power.

The earlier Dikshit-led Congress government provides concessions to 
households consuming up to 400 units. The subsidy already in place cost the 
government Rs 550 crore.


Conclusion
------------
In sum, I refuse to see this as a mass subsidy. Telescopic pricing is 
anything but that. It is ensuring that heavy consumers pay for making the 
basic usage of a fundamental (and scarce) resource free for all who use it 
responsibly within reasonable restrictions.
Doesn't these measures sound like populist politics that we have seen over 
the years which is the cause of our present day problem? Where is the 
revolution that everyone is talking about?
But in the end, nothing is free. Someone has to pay the price for free.﻿

A must-read, for all those who kind of know there is something fishy out 
there. And for those too, who are already aware of the larger picture, the 
whole game plan and have not fallen for the trap. I'm sure these are the 
categories of people who gave BJP those 32 seats. 

But I still see many gullible upper middle-class educated people 
patronizing AAP. On Twitter, on FB, during the discussions...Every time AK 
gets flak, their bhakti increases multi-fold. For instance, they don't see 
that AK is running away from accepting the challenge by of asking those 18 
questions, but rather feel proud of their leader for his fearlessness to 
challenge the big establishments. Irony! 

Of course we can only pray that CONgress gives support in spite of those 18 
q's, that AAP forms govt and fall flat and that there is no need to 
convince the people that were fooled. But what if it does not happen that 
way? AAP can then become a decisive factor in LS elections, without having 
proved anything. With the only skill-set that they "appear" 
anti-establishment. That is disastrous. I just hope BJP doesn't take it 
lightly, and starts taking counter-measures ASAP.

कोंग्रेस को नहीं मिलेगा , साथ ही जो लोग करप्शन से उब चुके है वे कोंग्रेस को 
सबक सिखाएंगे . ये वोये बीजेपी में जाने से रोकने के लिए केजरीवाल को ईमानदार 
कि मूर्त बना के पेश किया जा रहा है . कोंग्रेस को क्रिस्चन , मुसलिम या जाती 
के ना पर अस्थानीय विधायको को वोट मिल सकता है . कोंग्रेस उसी तरफ बढ़ रही है . 
डेल्ही के सफलता के बाद कोंग्रेस केजरीवाल को २०१४ के चुनाओ में उपयोग करने जा 
रही है इसलिए केजरीवाल को दूध का धूला दिखाना जरूरी है . केजरीवाल बड़ा सातिर 
है उसने दुनिया कि सबसे करप्ट पार्टी कोंग्रेस के भस्टाचार को बीजेपी के बराबर 
बता कर देश कि जनता तो ठगा है . और एक बात और याद रखे बिकी हुयी मीडिया जिस 
डेल्ही विधान सभा जीत को आम आदमी पार्टी कि जीत बता रही है वो दरसल कोंग्रेस 
कि हार है क्यों कि कोंग्रेस डेल्ही विधान सभा हारने वाली है ये बात तो मीडिया 
के सर्वे तब से बता रहे थे जब केजरीवाल ने डेल्ही विधान सभा लड़ने का फैसला भी 
नहीं लिया था . मुझे याद है जब एक मीडिया सर्वे ने BJP को ७० में से ५५ सीट 
देते हुए दवा किया था कि ये BJP के इतिहास कि एक बड़ी जीत होगी , ठीक इशके २४ 
घंटे बाद केजरीवाल का ब्यान आगया था कि वे डेल्ही विधानसभा चुनाओ लरना चाहते 
है . आप ने कोंग्रेस को हराया ही नहीं कोंग्रेस तो ऐसे भी हारनेवाली थी आप ने 
डेल्ही विधान सभा में बीजेपी के बहुमत को रोका . केजरीवाल तो कोंग्रेस का 
एजेंट है ही लेकिन मीडिया को पैसा खिला के पढ़े लिखे मूर्खो को बेवकूफ बना रहा 
है . आम आदमी पार्टी वाले कहते है कि "पहले इलेक्शन हारने के लिए लड़ना चाहिए " 
मतलब साफ़ है कि अपने इतने सीट के बारे में आम वाले खुद नहीं सोचे थे वे तो 
सिर्फ BJP का वोट काट के कोंग्रेस का रास्ता आसान करना चाहते थे . अब कोंग्रेस 
ईश एक्सपरिमेंट को पुरे देश में २०१४ में लागू करने जा रही है . केजरीवाल एक 
देशद्रोही है लेकिन बिकी मीडिया और कोंग्रेस के हाँथ कि सरकारी एजेंसीज उसे 
ईमानदार साबित करने में तुले रहते है . आज कि केजरीवाल कि एक्टिंग तो बेजोड़ थी 
क्या दिमाग है ईश देश के दुश्मन के पास ?? केजरीवाल कितना मीडिया को खरीद चूका 
है अगर जांचना है तो जब मीडिया पर डिबेट हो रहा हो तो देखे कितने न्यूज़ 
रिपोर्टर किसी को आप के नेता के खिलाफ बोलने भी नहीं देते अगर केजरीवाल या

okay well said... Modi has done good work in gujarat...no doubt abt 
that....what I want to tell you is that you dont understand what AAP is 
offering.....they are offering an alternate politics. you need to 
understand what are the problems of the country but you also need to know 
why these problems arose in the first place...
1. Swaraj - Acc to AAP ideology there should be targeted policy rather than 
national policy...you should read about decentralisation a little bit...
2. Funding - AAP has made their funding transparent whereas other parties 
are against it..so it gives me a feeling that intensions of  traditional 
parties are not clean
3. candidates-AAP selects its candidates on a criteria (honest, no serious 
criminal case) and put in public and then they ask public whether these 
candidates are right.if anyone brings a complain they inequire it. do u 
know AAP fought elections on 69 seats in delhi then  70 seats because two 
days before they found a candidate has some charge on him and they removed 
him..
Other parties have no criteria..
4. Experience- no doubt AAP have less experience..but there are lot of 
people in our country who can be leaders and govern our country. if AAP is 
able to reach these people they can really make an impact on the national 
elections..there is a huge difference between rural and urban india..in 
rural area the local leaders matters most but in urban areas the fight is 
MODI vs Kejriwal vs Rahul...urban area people are foolish in this case...
5 Advantage (AAP over other parties)- AAP has various kinds of people like 
leftist, rightists, central, liberal etc...at first look it can look like a 
khichdi but it represents the mindset of our country,,, we have all kinds 
of people in our country.. you cant be a rightist or leftist party.. 
initially people expected congress to be like that...actually AAP is an 
alternative to congress not BJP...
In the debates you might have seen traditional parties saying that AAP is 
not clear in their ideology, national issues etc...but I think you cant 
have a clear stand on this issues. As Richard Feynman, the great physicist 
and Nobel Laureate said, 'The fact that you are not sure means that it is 
possible that there is another way, some day."﻿

men on the issues like his support from congress, Kashmir, Dharna he gives 
me all the reasons to hate him.
Now compare him with Modi as Rahul baba is not in the competition this time.
When Modi became the CM, his first promise was to provide water into 
Narmada canal, and he fulfilled his promise facing the hurdles from 
Congress in the Centre. He never went for Dharna like Kejariwal for the 
injustice of Congress to Gujarat, for Gas, water, POTA or GUJCOKE etc etc.

Media is criticising him from last 10 years but he never blamed media like 
Kajariwal.
People love him because he has proved himself in almost each and every part 
of the state doesn't matter its rural or urban.
If you are out of Gujarat, please go on his website and see online the work 
he has done which we can see on the ground. His work in agriculture, 
malnutrition, education, health sector, infrastructure, women impowerment 
has got very little coverage on national media.
He stand by the people in flood in Surat, earthquake in Kutcch and during 
riots in the State. Before 2002 Hindus have suffered a lot in the State.

to deliver. He just wants people to trust him on this words which Modi has 
won through his work.
Kejariwal is in a hurry to get power in Centre. Otherwise he should wait 
and show his performance in Delhi. If he deserve it, people will definately 
give him a chance but this is not the time.
We have tried Modi and he is extremely  powerful to give governance, 
security and growth.

Know the Truth : The allegations about financial benefits to Adani group 
company are baseless. Adani Grou has been given 1700 ha land for the 
development of port and related works on 30 years lease on BOT basis. Every 
year rent is taken, and after 30 years this land would be a developed land 
and the prices worth crores would be returned to the state government.
Another 500 has land was allotted to set up a railway line so that the port 
could be connected to north India, and it is this decision which has 
resulted into 250 million cargo transport through this port, and 33,000 
crore custom duty income to the central government.
The government of India has approved 10,000 ha land for Adani SEZ, of which 
only 5590 ha land has been allotted. Rest of the land will be allotted in 
future is need arises, but its continuously growing prices will be earned 
by the Gujarat government. Thus the state has protected its future 
financial gain.”
“Gujarat has provision of transparent land allotment system, and policy to 
decide the land prices. Even Supreme Court has approved and admired state 
government’s transparent procedure on land.
In past, Congress government had allotted lands to industries at throwaway 
prices. Shankarsinh Vaghela had allotted 33 lakh square meter land at a 
price of Re.1 to industries. In one case, then Chief Minister had extended 
1.50 lakh square meter land allotment proposal to 3 lakh square meter. 
While the present Chief Minister has not allotted the land at price as low 
as Re.1 to anybody.
The land allotted to Adani group is non-productive, non-agriculture, padtar 
land and large part of that land comes under submerged area of sea. It is 
the central government that has given all permissions. Adani group has 
developed the land to use it. Present government has not acquired any land 
from the farmers to allot it to this company. Not only this but the state 
government has charged 25 times higher rates compare to previous 
governments while allotting the land. Thus the allegations of allotting 
land to Adani in Kutch at Rs 300 per square meter price are baseless.
PPA agreement with Adani on purchase of power from Adani Energy Power was 
done in February, 2007 and as per the agreement, Adani was to be paid Rs 
2.35 paise per unit for power. This was the lowest rate in entire country, 
and Gujarat Electricity Board had decided to purchase 1000 MW power through 
competitive tender bid in which Adani Power had quoted the lowest price to 
provide power. Adani Power plant purchases imported coal and supplies power 
to Gujarat government for Rs 2.35 paise per unit. As this rate was not 
affordable to Adani, the company had gone to Gujarat Electricity Regular 
Commission(GERC) for rate hike nod, but GERC had rejected Adani’s 
application. Adani went to tribunal in appeal where again its plea was 
rejected. Other than this, as per one more PPA agreement, electricity is 
purchased from Adani at competitive lowest price of Rs 2.89 per unit. Thus 
the allegations against Narendra Modi on power purchase from Adani can not 
last on any basis.﻿

tell us?

Gujarat govt did not supply any coal to Adani.

vested interest. All these parties are ignoring the welfare of the Armed 
Forces Personnel, Ex-Servicemen, Farmers, Agricultural/farm workers, poor 
and middle class families. All these classes are the victims under the 
false promises made not only in their respective manifestos but also 
projecting the farce welfare schemes while seeking votes in the elections. 
Especially the Ex-Soldiers and Farmers are most effected classes in the 
hands of these callous politicians.

We have formed a national political party on 1st  May, 2000 in the name and 
style of         ‘Jawan-Kisan Morcha Party’ with an intention to save all 
these victimized people from the clutches of fraudulent political leaders 
and bring them under one umbrella as united to fight together against these 
anti-poor-farmers-Armed Forces Personnel. The founders of this party are 
Capt (Retd) Jageswar Prasad and Dr. Janardhan from Bihar State. 
Subsequently this party had been got registered U/Section 29-A of the 
 Representation People Act, 1951 with the Central Election Commission vide 
 Regd No. 56/381/2000 TS-III/2803 dt 05-09-2001 dt. 05-09-2001 as one of 
the national political parties.

This party was started as a social welfare organization, with firm 
determination to bring a change in the atmosphere of Indian national 
politics through revolution and liberate the people from who had become 
feudalists and capitalists after being elected. This party is in operations 
over the past 13 years. The constitution of our party enshrined with a 
prime clause to protect the rights of all Jawans - Kisans  along with other 
welfare  of several goals . 
Jawan-Kisan Morcha is one of the largest Indian political organizations. 
This party provides the platform to young talented Jawan, Kisan and youth 
from other sectors like doctors, engineers, lawyers, teachers, women etc., 
to serve the nation, flourish our Indian values, culture and to evolve true 
Indian democracy.
Jawan-Kisan Morcha is constantly working and aims to encourage Jawan, Kisan 
and youth from other segments to participate in Indian politics and create 
a corruption and crime free Indian socio-economic infrastructure.


2. PRINCIPLES:

To unite the unlimited power of Jawans & Kisans, to e-establish corruption 
free welfare oriented socialist nation, unite the public opinion and to 
solve the public problems by simple actions. This is the belief of 
‘Morcha’, ensure removal of ill thoughts, with the help of strong will 
power and by improving action by self is the principle of ‘Morcha’. 

3. AIMS:  

The Armed Formed Personnel, Ex-Servicemen, farmers, agricultural laborers, 
weaker sections, middle class families are being cheated by the selfish 
political parties in our country. Primarily the Ex-Servicemen and farmers 
are being neglected by these political parties. To bring all of the 
victimized people into one unit and to protect our constitutional rights, 
this Jawan-Kisan Morcha is formed into a political party with an aim to:-

a). with the help of strong unity of ex-servicemen, retired personnel of 
para military forces, farmers and common men, the development and security 
of society can be ensured. The      lower class and middle class establish 
welfare services to reestablish social welfare state which will be free 
from corruption with no place for hatred or terrorism to improve the image 
of the nation. The nation wide high cultural development of agriculture and 
live-stock to the  maximum. To preserve the unity of the nation, 
educational, character, humanity scientifically and strategically strong, 
prosperous and physically strong with increased capability. To remove the 
new feudal system formed with the connivance of selfish, corrupt, useless 
politicians and criminals. 

b).  the industrialists inculcate the habit of superior quality of 
production and proper distribution with reasonable cost, they must become 
good businessmen, develop sense of responsibility among themselves about 
society and the nation to make India a super power in world of trade and 
commerce.

c).  raise mutual respect for all religions, respect for all persons 
irrespective of case and creed 
     and increase sense of duty.

d). establish similar system of imparting education, equal opportunity and 
generate  
      employment. 

e). make India ‘Global Guru’ with the help of mental, psychical, social, 
cultural and political 
     revolution. 

f). to remove communal feeling, caste frenzy and bigotry.

g). to stop misuse of constitution, law, judiciary, legislative, executive, 
police and military power 
     and get equal justice to the people at large.

h). for useful all round development of the country develop sense of 
service, self dependence
     and allegiances to nation in common man and the youth. Bring awakening 
about 
     agriculture, industry and political thinking in ex-servicemen, for the 
continuous prosperity of
     the nation.

i). in social aspects eradicating the social evils, disruptive activities 
prevailing in society.

j). to safeguard the religious sentiment, traditions of each individual.

k). bring disinclination in world community regarding destructive thinking 
and guide it towards
     constructive thinking.

l). to end the system based on caste and creed, establish system based on 
social and 
    economic equality.

m). to use extraordinary and genius personalities in nation building.

n). Jawan-Kisan Morcha will have full faith in constitution, socialism, 
secularism and 
     democratic principles and keep the sovereignty and unity of the 
country intact. 
 
4. OBJECTIVES:

(01). To provide the welfare and protect the rights of service and 
ex-servicemen, farmers and agricultural laborers,  middle class families, 
industrial and factory workers.

(02). To protect the property rights, employees’ safety, eradicate the 
gratuitous difference between employers and their employees, farmers, 
agricultural laborers and to improve the per capita income of the citizens 
by establishing more industries which can generate more employment 
opportunities in the country in equitable manner.

 (03). To form into leaders of selfless Govt, simple life style with 
service motto who can provide us welfare measures in all spheres of life 
 for uplift of  children’ future.

(04). Not only to protect the rich and traditional Indian socio-economic 
and culture  but also find a prominent place the name of our country on the 
world map.

(05). To safeguard the sovereignty of India, its scientific development, 
its technological forwardness, historical and physical Indian culture 
amongst other developed countries.

(06). To bow-down to Indian Judiciary and  fight against injustice and 
provide equality and justice to all citizens.

(07). To distribute the knowledge of our science & technology to the 
downtrodden from upper castes.

(08). To take forward our great India with its economy, scientific 
development, defence and dynamic lives of Indians to the other countries to 
respect our culture.

(10). To get all the communities into united India to face any future 
consequences to our India.

(11). To get all the castes, communities, religions  into one United India 
to face any future consequences to our India.  

(12). To provide adequate safety and protection to the lives and properties 
of the poor and middle class people.

(13). To provide guarantee of employment all eligible citizens with 
suitable wages/salaries and social infrastructure.

(14). Totally eliminate communal riots in the country.

(15). Upheld the immemorial centuries old social and customary laws and 
traditions.

(16). Not only condemn the terrorism, Maoism, Naxalism but also co-operate 
with the Govt agencies to route out completely from our country.

(17). To elect and vote for those who are selfless with high morals and 
values to be their leaders who can provide the best administration in the 
country.

(18).  To bring reforms in the police and judicial administration

(20). Judiciary must act as per peoples aspirations not otherwise.

A. Morcha believes in systematic, social development and to achieve its 
ideal, to make use of legal peaceful, constitutional and democratic methods.
B. To establish direct communication between people and the government.
C. Morcha desires to establish welfare-state adopting constitutional and

D. Morcha is not supporter of the system established on caste, religions

S. Morcha favors the ‘Code of Conduct; imposed by the election commission

10. The scholars will be given their due respect.

लिए मैगसेसे का पुरस्कार मिला।


यह पुरस्कार फोर्ड फाउंडेशन की मदद से ही सन् 2000 में शुरू किया गया था। 
केजरीवाल के प्रत्येक कदम में फोर्ड फाउंडेशन की भूमिका रही है। पहले उन्हें 
38 साल की उम्र में 50,000 डॉलर का यह पुरस्कार मिला, लेकिन उनकी एक भी 
उपलब्धि का विवरण इस पुरस्कार के साथ नहीं था।

विभिन्न श्रेणियों में मैगसेसे पुरस्कार रोकफेलर ब्रदर्स फाउंडेशन ने स्थापित 
किया था। 

इस पुरस्कार के साथ मिलने वाली नगद राशि का बड़ा हिस्सा फोर्ड फाउंडेशन ही 
देता है। 
आश्चर्यजनक रूप से केजरीवाल जब सरकारी सेवा में थे, तब भी फोर्ड उनकी संस्था 
को आर्थिक मदद पहुंचा रहा था।
केजरीवाल ने मनीष सिसोदिया के साथ मिलकर 1999 में ‘कबीर’ नामक एक संस्था का 
गठन किया था।
हैरानी की बात है कि जिस फोर्ड फाउंडेशन ने आर्थिक दान दिया, वही संस्था उसे 
सम्मानित भी कर रही थी। ऐसा लगता है कि यह सब एक सोची समझी रणनीति का हिस्सा 
थी।

फोर्ड ने अपने इस कदम से भारत के जनमानस में अपना एक आदमी गढ़ दिया। केजरीवाल 
फोर्ड फाउंडेशन द्वारा निर्मित एक महत्वपूर्ण आदमी बन गए। 

हैरानी की बात यह भी है कि ‘कबीर’ पारदर्शी होने का दावा करती है, लेकिन इस 
संस्था ने साल 2008-9 में मिलने वाले विदेशी धन का व्योरा अपनी वेबसाइट पर 
नहीं दिया है, जबकि फोर्ड फाउंडेशन से मिली जानकारी बताती है कि उन्होंने 
‘कबीर’को 2008 में 1.97 लाख डॉलर दिए।

इससे साफ होता है कि फोर्ड फाउंडेशन ने 2005 में अपना एजेंडा आगे बढ़ाने के 
लिए अरविंद केजरीवाल को चुना। उसकी सारी गतिविधियों का खर्च वहन किया। इतना ही 
नहीं, बल्कि मैगससे पुरस्कार दिलवाकर चर्चा में भी लाया।

एक ‘बियॉन्ड हेडलाइन्स’ नामक वेबसाइट ने ‘सूचना के अधिकार कानून’ के जरिए 
‘कबीर’ को विदेशी धन मिलने की जानकारी मांगी। इस जानकारी के अनुसार ‘कबीर’ को 
2007 से लेकर 2010 तक फोर्ड फाउंडेशन से 86,61,742 रुपए मिले हैं। कबीर को धन 
देने वालों की सूची में एक ऐसा भी नाम है, जिसे पढ़कर हर कोई चौंक जाएगा। यह 
नाम डच दूतावास का है।

यहां सवाल उठता है कि आखिर डच दूतावास से अरविंद केजरीवाल का क्या संबंध है? 
क्योंकि डच दूतावास हमेशा ही भारत में संदेह के घेरे में रहा है। 16 अक्टूबर, 
2012 को अदालत ने तहलका मामले में आरोप तय किए हैं। इस पूरे मामले में जिस लेख 
को आधार बनाया गया है, उसमें डच की भारत में गतिविधियों को संदिग्ध बताया गया 
है।

इसके अलावा सवाल यह भी उठता है कि किसी देश का दूतावास किसी दूसरे देश की अनाम 
संस्था को सीधे धन कैसे दे सकता है? आखिर डच दूतावास का अरविंद केजरीवाल और 
मनीष सिसोदिया से क्या रिश्ता है? यह रहस्य है। न तो स्वयं अरविंद और न ही टीम 
अरविंद ने इस बाबत कोई जानकारी दी है।

इतना ही नहीं, बल्कि 1985 में पीएसओ नाम की एक संस्था बनाई गई थी। इस संस्था 
का काम विकास में सहयोग के नाम पर विशेषज्ञों को दूसरे देशों में तैनात करना 
था। पीएसओ को डच विदेश मंत्रालय सीधे धन देता है। पीएसओ हिओस समेत 60 डच विकास 
संगठनों का समूह है। नीदरलैंड सरकार इसे हर साल 27 मिलियन यूरो देती है। पीएसओ 
‘प्रिया’ संस्था का आर्थिक सहयोगी है। प्रिया का संबंध फोर्ड फाउंडेशन से है। 
यही ‘प्रिया’ केजरीवाल और मनीष सिसोदिया की संस्था ‘कबीर’ की सहयोगी है।

इन सब बातों से साफ है कि डच एनजीओ, फोर्ड फाउंडेशन,डच सरकार और केजरीवाल के 
बीच परस्पर संबंध है। इतना ही नहीं, कई देशों से शिकायत मिलने के बाद पीएसओ को 
बंद किया जा रहा है। ये शिकायतें दूसरे देशों के आंतरिक मामलों में हस्तक्षेप 
से संबंधित हैं। 2011 में पीएसओ की आम सभा ने इसे 1 जनवरी, 2013 को बंद करने 
का निर्णय लिया है। यह निर्णय दूसरे देशों की उन्हीं शिकायतों का असर माना जा 
रहा है।

हाल ही में पायनियर नामक अंग्रेजी दैनिक अखबार ने कहा कि हिवोस ने गुजरात के 
विभिन्न गैर सरकारी संगठन को अप्रैल 2008 और अगस्त 2012 के बीच 13 लाख यूरो 
यानी सवा नौ करोड़ रुपए दिए। हिवोस पर फोर्ड फाउंडेशन की सबसे ज्यादा कृपा 
रहती है। डच एनजीओ हिवोस इंटरनेशनल इंस्टीट्यूट ऑफ सोशल साइंस द हेग (एरासमस 
युनिवर्सिटी रोटरडम) से पिछले पांच सालों से सहयोग ले रही है। हिवोस ने 
“परिवर्तन” को भी धन मुहैया कराया है।

इस संस्था की खासियत यह है कि विभिन्न देशों में सत्ता के खिलाफ जनउभार पैदा 
करने की इसे विशेषज्ञता हासिल है। डच सरकार के इस पूरे कार्यक्रम का समन्वय 
आईएसएस के डॉ.क्रीस बिकार्ट के हवाले है। इसके साथ-साथ मीडिया को साधने के लिए 
एक संस्था खड़ी की गई है। इस संस्था के दक्षिणी एशिया में सात कार्यालय हैं। 
जहां से इनकी गतिविधियां संचालित होती हैं। इस संस्था का नाम ‘पनोस’ है।

possible” asKejriwal is indeed the Anil Kapoor of Nayak, let’s take the

society.

The
answer lies in the following objective type questioning we are used to in 
our competition exams!

Q.
What sort of leader you want? How would like your father to be?

Choice 1:
An idealist who lives a clean – corruption free life and delivers 21st 
century socialism by providing free bijlee, paani. The AK Hangal of our 
politics.

Choice 2:
A visionary who lives a cleaner and proven and endured corruption free life 
and delivers growth and development. Does not provides free bijlee to even 
farmers, rather uses this revenue collected to deliver a more progressive 
and development friendly governance.

Q.
Who can secure you better from an ever hostile neighborhood with 2 hostile 
and nuclear weapon countries with which we have already fought 4 wars?

Choice 1:
An escapist / effete leader who can’t take decisions on his own and starts 
blabbering and bad mouthing his opponents when pushed to the wall

Choice 2:
A strong man who stands and speaks while bombs are going off near him and 
do not indulge in rabble rousing about the bombs going on, should the 
massive crowd of over 7 lacs not get excited and a major stampede / rioting 
doesn’t happen. A man who withstood an entire Government machinery and 
media / NGO demonization for about 15 years and yet does not utter a single 
foul word
against any one.

Q.
Who would you need to take economy to where it needs to be?

Choice 1:
A leftist who thrives on frugality. One who is happy to live a saintly life 
and wants to be happy in what you have rather than engineer your inner self 
to achieve greatness and prosperity in life.

Choice 2:
A man of action who understands the good things of life and wants to 
deliver it to you. A life where NO dream is “compromise” and where we all 
get 21st century material comforts with hard work and skill development.

Q.
Who can remove poverty from this country and make us rich?

Choice 1:
An eternal agitator whose idea of Governance is entire negativity in total 
and who will bottle neck the system with his over the top ideas of 
controlling the “ corruption”. One who will strangle the system with his 
farcical idealism and hence discourage industrialization and 
entrepreneurship.

Choice 2: An
eternal optimistic and fighter who knows that ONLY way to eliminate poverty 
is to provide support to rich! Salvation of a worker is not in closing of 
or opposing of “rich corporate” but is in encouraging “rich corporate” to 
invest more, surely in a transparent and corruption free manner.

Q.
What do you want in 2025 for your generations to come?

Choice 1:
A 21st century version of erstwhile Soviet Union which was laidback, slow 
and regressive state, ironically more corrupt than USA in terms of 
prevalence of corruption in daily lives!

Choice 2:
An Advance version of United States of America which is bustling, vibrant, 
competitive and front runner in the league of the nations.

Again
I leave it on your individual discretions and choices as to what you would 
like to go with.

However
if you have mostly chosen the Choice 2, please share this post and among as 
much people as you can.

Please
note that small individual efforts when pooled together become a great team 
victory !

Please
do whatever you can do to have this great nation achieve its greatness by 
having Modi as the prime minister of this country!

KEJRIWAL VS NARENDAR MODI – THE REAL PICTURE?

For all those “neo fans” of Kejriwal and the political fence sitters who 
feel that the above narrative is “too negative” to be true and “is not 
possible” asKejriwal is indeed the Anil Kapoor of Nayak, let’s take the 
picture in this way only and try to assess the two.

Well
if it is so, I must say that Kejriwal comes across as a fresh current of 
air in the bad jungle of Indian politics which is dominated by corruption, 
case, criminalization and all and anything which is bad and immoral in the 
society.

Now whom should I vote? Arvind Kejriwal OR Narendar Modi?

The
answer lies in the following objective type questioning we are used to in 
our competition exams!

Q.
What sort of leader you want? How would like your father to be?

Choice 1:
An idealist who lives a clean – corruption free life and delivers 21st 
century socialism by providing free bijlee, paani. The AK Hangal of our 
politics.

Choice 2:
A visionary who lives a cleaner and proven and endured corruption free life 
and delivers growth and development. Does not provides free bijlee to even 
farmers, rather uses this revenue collected to deliver a more progressive 
and development friendly governance.

Q.
Who can secure you better from an ever hostile neighborhood with 2 hostile 
and nuclear weapon countries with which we have already fought 4 wars?

Choice 1:
An escapist / effete leader who can’t take decisions on his own and starts 
blabbering and bad mouthing his opponents when pushed to the wall

Choice 2:
A strong man who stands and speaks while bombs are going off near him and 
do not indulge in rabble rousing about the bombs going on, should the 
massive crowd of over 7 lacs not get excited and a major stampede / rioting 
doesn’t happen. A man who withstood an entire Government machinery and 
media / NGO demonization for about 15 years and yet does not utter a single 
foul word
against any one.

Q.
Who would you need to take economy to where it needs to be?

Choice 1:
A leftist who thrives on frugality. One who is happy to live a saintly life 
and wants to be happy in what you have rather than engineer your inner self 
to achieve greatness and prosperity in life.

Choice 2:
A man of action who understands the good things of life and wants to 
deliver it to you. A life where NO dream is “compromise” and where we all 
get 21st century material comforts with hard work and skill development.

Q.
Who can remove poverty from this country and make us rich?

Choice 1:
An eternal agitator whose idea of Governance is entire negativity in total 
and who will bottle neck the system with his over the top ideas of 
controlling the “ corruption”. One who will strangle the system with his 
farcical idealism and hence discourage industrialization and 
entrepreneurship.

Choice 2: An
eternal optimistic and fighter who knows that ONLY way to eliminate poverty 
is to provide support to rich! Salvation of a worker is not in closing of 
or opposing of “rich corporate” but is in encouraging “rich corporate” to 
invest more, surely in a transparent and corruption free manner.

Q.
What do you want in 2025 for your generations to come?

Choice 1:
A 21st century version of erstwhile Soviet Union which was laidback, slow 
and regressive state, ironically more corrupt than USA in terms of 
prevalence of corruption in daily lives!

Choice 2:
An Advance version of United States of America which is bustling, vibrant, 
competitive and front runner in the league of the nations.

Again
I leave it on your individual discretions and choices as to what you would 
like to go with.

However
if you have mostly chosen the Choice 2, please share this post and among as 
much people as you can.

Please
note that small individual efforts when pooled together become a great team 
victory !

Please
do whatever you can do to have this great nation achieve its greatness by 
having Modi as the prime minister of this country!
